===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|mokken|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|mocquer||to deride, jeer|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|dum|en}} {{term|mocken||to mumble|lang=dum}} or {{etyl|gml|en}} {{term|mucken||to grumble, talk with the mouth half-opened|lang=gml}}, both from {{etyl|osx|en}} *{{term||mokkian, *mukkian|to low, mumble|lang=osx}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*mukkijaną}}, {{term/t|gem-pro|*mūhaną||to low, bellow, shout}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*mūg-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*mūk-||to low, mumble}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|firmucken||to be stupid|lang=goh}}, Modern {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|mucksen||to utter a word|lang=de}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} dialectal {{term|mokkel||kiss|lang=nl}}.

